        <h1 itemprop="headline">How Do I Get To the Circuit Boards in a TV?</h1>
         
    </header>
    <section itemprop="articleBody">
        <p>The circuit boards in virtually every television set are accessible by removing the rear (back) cover.  The back cover is held in place with screws, which are commonly Philips-head.  On the old consoles and projection TVs the back covers were easy to remove.</p>
        @Html.Partial("Article/FlatScreenRepairPreparation")
        <br />
        <p>If you plan on powering up the TV with the back cover removed, take heed to the following warning.</p>
        <br />@Html.Partial("Article/DangerHighVoltage")
